<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-16797] Incompatible constants related to forwarded writes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16797</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The header for forwarded writes changed from 3.x.x-&amp;gt;4.0. In C* 3.x.x headers are &quot;FWD_TO&quot; or &quot;FWD_FROM&quot; while in C* 4.0 headers are &quot;FORWARD_TO&quot; or &quot;FORWARD_FROM&quot;. Therefore, I suppose that there will be a failure during rolling upgrade from 3.x.x to 4.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
